---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Internal Sprint 02 — Signal Normalization';
---

<BaseLayout title={title}>
  <section class="runbook internal">
    <div class="banner">Internal Use Only</div>

    <h1>Assessment System Contract — v1</h1>

    <h2>Purpose</h2>
    <p>
      This contract defines how QA automation frameworks are assessed,
      scored, and routed into the sprint system. It ensures consistency,
      repeatability, and client-aligned interpretation.
    </p>

    <h2>System Layers</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Execution Layer</strong> — produces raw validation output</li>
      <li><strong>Interpretation Layer</strong> — converts signals into structured data</li>
      <li><strong>Decision Layer</strong> — produces trust level and sprint routing</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Input Model</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Validation log (static scan + structure signals)</li>
      <li>Runtime signals (failures, release gate, domain)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Strength Classification</h2>
    <p>Strengths represent stable, repeatable system capabilities.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Must be observable from code or execution</li>
      <li>Must be reusable across multiple tests</li>
      <li>Confidence: low / medium / high</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Risk Classification</h2>
    <p>Risks represent gaps that impact reliability or release confidence.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>severity:</strong> low / medium / high</li>
      <li><strong>scope:</strong> localized / suite_partial / framework_wide</li>
      <li><strong>impact:</strong> flake / maintainability / release_blocking</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Runtime Signal Rules</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Runtime failures override static assumptions</li>
      <li>Multiple failures in same domain = single grouped risk</li>
      <li>Release gate BLOCK caps trust at medium</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Trust Scoring Model</h2>
    <pre>
base_score =
  (strength_count * 2)
  - (high_risk * 2)
  - (medium_risk * 1)
  - (low_risk * 0.5)
    </pre>

    <h3>Trust Levels</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>High:</strong> reliable, decision-ready system</li>
      <li><strong>Medium:</strong> usable, but key gaps exist</li>
      <li><strong>Low:</strong> unreliable or misleading signal</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Caps</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Release BLOCK → max trust = medium</li>
      <li>≥ 4 strengths → cannot be low unless system is unstable</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Sprint Routing Rules</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>State lifecycle issues → Sprint 5</li>
      <li>Release gate ambiguity → Sprint 6</li>
      <li>Maintainability / locator drift → Sprint 8</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Client Narrative Rule</h2>
    <p>
      Output must describe the system as:
      <br />
      <strong>"Working but incomplete"</strong> when strengths exist but
      release confidence is limited.
    </p>

    <h2>Non-Goals</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No full AI capability modeling</li>
      <li>No overfitting to tool-specific patterns</li>
      <li>No punitive scoring for partial maturity</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Version</h2>
    <p>v1 — Initial calibrated contract</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .internal {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: auto;
  }

  .banner {
    background: #7f1d1d;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 10px 16px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  pre {
    background: #111827;
    padding: 16px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }
</style>
